      "text": "I believe when we look back at our current democratic and financial systems from the future (say a hundred years), we will \"remember\" \"democracy\" and \"money\" in much the same way that we currently perceive Morse code - as weirdly anachronistic. Perhaps that's not the right word - I would hope rather we keep a certain fondness if not amazement as to how this strange group of people ever thought we could govern a planet by shovelling around tokens mediated by advertisements. \n\nWe now have modern voice, video and internet based communication - Morse code was great in it's day, but with an impossibly primitive interface, and completely unable to capture a whole range of human value."
